9 An Act relating to state government; creating the
Oklahoma State Agency, Board, and Commission Review
10 Task Force; designating membership of task force;
requiring task force to perform certain duties;
11 providing for the electronic submission of certain
report; providing for certain reimbursement of
12 members of task force; providing for codification;
and declaring an emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 8131 of Title 74, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. There is hereby created the Oklahoma State Agency, Board,
20 and Commission Review Task Force.
21 B. The task force shall consist of nine (9) members, three of
22 whom shall be appointed by the President Pro Tempore of the Senate,
23 three of whom shall be appointed by the Speaker of the House of
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1273 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Repr esentatives, and three of whom shall be appointed by the
2 Governor.
3 C. The President Pro Tempore of the Senate and the Speaker of
4 the House of Representatives shall designate co-chairs for the task
5 force from among their respective appointees.
6 D. Meetings shall be held at the call of the co-chairs. The
7 task force shall meet at such time as established by the co-chairs.
8 E. The task force shall:
9 1. Review the efficiency, effectiveness, and necessity of all
10 state agencies, boards, and commissions of this state; and
11 2. Provide recommendations to the Legislature for the
12 elimination, consolidation, or alteration of the duties of state
13 agencies, boards, and commissions of this state.
14 F. Any reports or recommendations of the task force shall be
15 electronically submitted to the President Pro Tempore of the Senate,
16 the Speaker of the House of Representatives, and the Governor, on or
17 before January 31, 2027, and annually thereafter.
18 G. Staffing for the task force shall be provided jointly by the
19 staff of the Senate and the House of Representatives.
20 H. Members of the task force shall serve without compensation
21 but may be reimbursed by the appointed authority for necessary
22 travel pursuant to the State Travel Reimbursement Act.
23 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
